Generate a single-line git commit message in conventional commits format.
Output ONLY the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

Format: type(scope): description

Write the description in the style of William Shakespeare — Early Modern English,
dramatic flair, iambic cadence where it fits. The type(scope) prefix must remain
standard conventional commits format. Only the description gets the Shakespearean treatment.

Rules:
- Under 72 characters total
- Use the correct type and scope from the diff
- Scope is REQUIRED: choose the primary component or subsystem
- Valid types: feat, fix, refactor, chore, ci, build, test, docs, style, perf
- The description must be factually accurate — the drama is in the language
- Use Early Modern English: hath, doth, wherefore, henceforth, forsooth, etc.

Examples of the spirit (do NOT copy literally — generate from the actual diff):
  fix(parser): hark, the null doth crash our noble code no more
  feat(auth): henceforth, tokens shall guard the kingdom's gate
  chore(deps): cast out the old and usher in the new packages
  refactor(api): untangle this most wretched knot of logic
  test(config): prove with tests that all doth function well
